  "text": "the average steady-state reduction of I Ba peak amplitude for concentrations of -AgaTxIVA Ն100 nM was 74 Ϯ 4% (n ϭ 21 neurons). The effect of -AgaTxIVA was not reversed after a Ն5-min washing (data not shown) and was not reversed by depolarizing prepulses (Fig. 5B) in contrast with the observation of [CITATION_1] in rat neurons. The persistence of a residual current in high concentrations of -AgaTxIVA (Ն100 nM) suggests the presence in these neurons of an -AgaTxIVA-resistant current component.",
